sentences: Beans (born Robert Edward Stewart II) is a rapper from White Plains, New York.
Beans has collaborated with Vernon Reid of Living Colour, Kool A.D., Ghislain Poirier, Arto Lindsay, Alec Empire, Funkstörung, Holy Fuck, Evil Nine, DJ Shadow among others.
In 2013, Beans collaborated with Ghostly International recording artist, Mux Mool, under the name, Knifefight.
The second album, Love Me Tonight, features various producers such as Sam Fogarino from Interpol, Gobby, Laurel Halo, Container, Ben Chisholm (Chelsea Wolfe), Tobacco, and Pete Swanson.
Beans has been known to perform in a wide variety of venues, from underground clubs in New York's East Village to festivals worldwide.
In the past has taken to the stage armed with only a microphone and a portable CD player for his backing track, further reflecting the minimalist nature of his style.
He has been recently performing and touring with That Kid Prolific.
